The Federal Government has said Nigeria is not in any way near a debt crisis despite its $81.27 billion (about N24.947 trillion) debts but has a revenue generation problem.  Minister of Finance, Budget and National Planning, Mrs. Zainab Ahmed, who made this disclosure at a two-day Public Hearing on the 2020 Appropriation Bill convened by the joint Senate and House committees Appropriation explained that despite the debt profile, the country's total borrowing rate was 20% of its Gross Domestic Product (GDP). Our Correspondent reports that the minister said the budget deficit of N2.7 trillion in 2020 was to be financed mainly by borrowing.  In their opening remarks, President of the Senate, Ahmad Lawan, and Speaker of the House of Representatives, Femi Gbajabiamila, said the move to return to a January to December budget cycle will allow for proper planning and implementation.